  "texts": [
    "We fit the simulated single-band light curves using EzTaoX to infer τ DRW and σ DRW, following the strategy outlined in Section 3.1.2.",
    "To avoid potential prior-driven biases, we extend the upper limit of the MCMC prior on τ DRW to 10 5 days-an order of magnitude longer than the lightcurve baseline.",
    "Based on our simulations, EzTaoX recovers τ DRW without systematic bias up to one tenth of the lightcurve baseline.",
    "Figure 9 displays the distribution of ∆ log(τ DRW)-the difference between the recovered and input log(τ DRW)-as a function of the recovered τ DRWto-baseline ratio (ρ out).",
    "Plotting ρ out rather than ρ in is more informative, since the true τ DRW is unknown when fitting DRW models to real AGN light curves."
  ],
